    <section class="container" aria-labelledby="hero-title" style="padding-top:40px;padding-bottom:40px">
      <h1 id="hero-title">A Trust‑First Communications Thesis for Kooul</h1>
      <p class="mb-2"><strong>Hook.</strong> I’ve spent the last year working alongside a market leader in Morocco’s platform economy, watching the sector mature and embed itself in the Kingdom’s socio‑economic and political fabric. Kooul’s entry has been impressive — fast, disciplined, and clearly product‑led.</p>
      <p class="mb-2">My conviction: <em>trust</em> is the growth engine now. With strategic communications — public proof and clear positioning — we can strengthen stakeholder confidence where it matters most (rules, data, payment, quality, safety, service) and convert that confidence into acquisition, activation, and repeat.</p>
      <p class="mb-3">Below is a focused thesis for Kooul: six gaps where communications unlocks growth, the framing that connects them, and an outcome‑first 90‑day path to ship the right proofs.</p>
      <img class="hero-illustration" alt="Illustration placeholder" src="data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='1200' height='440'><rect width='100%25' height='100%25' fill='%23f3f4f6'/><text x='50%25' y='50%25' dominant-baseline='middle' text-anchor='middle' fill='%239ca3af' font-family='Inter, Arial' font-size='22'>Strategic context illustration</text></svg>"/>
      <div class="author" aria-label="Author">
        <img src="https://i.imgur.com/2McZdaQ.jpg" alt="Photo of Zakaria Gallouch" width="40" height="40" />
        <span class="name">Zakaria Gallouch</span>
        <span class="muted">Senior Strategic Communications & PR Consultant</span>
        <div class="actions">
          <a class="btn secondary sm" href="https://codepen.io/sahelpub21/full/ByjdErK" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Website</a>
          <a class="btn sm" href="https://yti.my.canva.site/zg-portfolio" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Portfolio</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Six strategic gaps -->
    <section class="container" id="gaps" aria-labelledby="gaps-title">
      <h2 id="gaps-title">Six strategic gaps where communications unlocks growth</h2>
      <div class="chips" aria-label="Core trust assets">
        <span class="chip">Fair‑Play Charter</span>
        <span class="chip">Privacy & Ranking Note</span>
        <span class="chip">Kooul Guarantee</span>
        <span class="chip">Quality & Traceability</span>
        <span class="chip">Rider Safety</span>
        <span class="chip">Care‑first Support</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cards-2" style="margin-top:16px">
        <div class="card">
          <img class="gap-ph" alt="Placeholder — Fair‑Play Charter" loading="lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='640' height='240'><rect width='100%25' height='100%25' fill='%23f3f4f6'/><text x='50%25' y='50%25' dominant-baseline='middle' text-anchor='middle' fill='%239ca3af' font-family='Inter, Arial' font-size='16'>Image — Fair‑Play Charter</text></svg>"/>
          <h3 class="mb-2">1) Legitimacy & competitive transparency</h3>
          <p class="muted mb-2"><strong>Observation:</strong> Morocco’s platform market is increasingly judged on fair‑play rules (non‑exclusivity, clear commissions, understandable ranking).</p>
          <p class="muted mb-2"><strong>Risk:</strong> Without a clear stance, Kooul operates under standards set by global giants — creating onboarding friction for restaurants and doubt among media/authorities.</p>
          <p class="mb-2"><strong>Strategic comms angle:</strong> Publish a bilingual (FR/AR) public charter that goes beyond minimum compliance: non‑exclusivity by principle, decoded fee structure, ranking principles, and a commitment to self‑audit.</p>
          <p class="mb-0"><strong>Growth impact:</strong> Fewer objections at signature (supply), higher local preference (acquisition), reduced reputation risk (media CAC).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <img class="gap-ph" alt="Placeholder — Privacy & Ranking Note" loading="lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='640' height='240'><rect width='100%25' height='100%25' fill='%23f3f4f6'/><text x='50%25' y='50%25' dominant-baseline='middle' text-anchor='middle' fill='%239ca3af' font-family='Inter, Arial' font-size='16'>Image — Privacy & Ranking</text></svg>"/>
          <h3 class="mb-2">2) Data & algorithm (privacy & explainability)</h3>
          <p class="muted mb-2"><strong>Observation:</strong> CNDP and consumers expect protection and explainability around ranking and promos — now core brand criteria.</p>
          <p class="muted mb-2"><strong>Risk:</strong> Perceived opacity triggers drop‑off during onboarding/app use and restaurant fear of being “down‑ranked”.</p>
          <p class="mb-2"><strong>Strategic comms angle:</strong> Formalize a Privacy & Ranking Note: purposes, retention, user rights, security; a simple diagram of ranking signals (relevance, distance, restaurant performance) and a clear explanation/appeal path.</p>
          <p class="mb-0"><strong>Growth impact:</strong> Higher install→first‑order conversion, fewer “ranking” tickets (support cost), improved restaurant retention (supply LTV).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <img class="gap-ph" alt="Placeholder — Kooul Guarantee" loading="lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='640' height='240'><rect width='100%25' height='100%25' fill='%23f3f4f6'/><text x='50%25' y='50%25' dominant-baseline='middle' text-anchor='middle' fill='%239ca3af' font-family='Inter, Arial' font-size='16'>Image — Kooul Guarantee</text></svg>"/>
          <h3 class="mb-2">3) Payment, cancellation & refunds (COD → digital)</h3>
          <p class="muted mb-2"><strong>Observation:</strong> COD persists because buyers fear losing money when quality/latency disappoints; payment options alone don’t erase perceived risk.</p>
          <p class="muted mb-2"><strong>Risk:</strong> Activation stalls at payment; NPS suffers if cancellation paths are unclear.</p>
          <p class="mb-2"><strong>Strategic comms angle:</strong> Visible <em>Kooul Guarantee</em>: if quality isn’t right, re‑delivery/refund; published refund SLA; step‑by‑step cancellation guide; monthly barometer (refund rate/average time/reasons).</p>
          <p class="mb-0"><strong>Growth impact:</strong> Higher digital payment share (activation), lower post‑incident churn (retention), reduced cash/logistics costs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <img class="gap-ph" alt="Placeholder — Quality & Traceability" loading="lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='640' height='240'><rect width='100%25' height='100%25' fill='%23f3f4f6'/><text x='50%25' y='50%25' dominant-baseline='middle' text-anchor='middle' fill='%239ca3af' font-family='Inter, Arial' font-size='16'>Image — Quality & Traceability</text></svg>"/>
          <h3 class="mb-2">4) Quality & traceability (restaurant → doorstep)</h3>
          <p class="muted mb-2"><strong>Observation:</strong> Trust is won on the last meter (time/temperature/packaging); ONSSA sets the frame, but customers judge what they can see.</p>
          <p class="muted mb-2"><strong>Risk:</strong> Without tangible signals, price/speed won’t sustain repeat.</p>
          <p class="mb-2"><strong>Strategic comms angle:</strong> Visible Quality Charter: sealed/insulated bags, pickup/drop‑off timestamps, hand‑over photo, transparent “non‑conform” protocol; publish a quality log (checks & fixes).</p>
          <p class="mb-0"><strong>Growth impact:</strong> Fewer claims/refunds (margin), higher D30 repeat (retention), more word‑of‑mouth (organic acquisition).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <img class="gap-ph" alt="Placeholder — Rider Safety" loading="lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='640' height='240'><rect width='100%25' height='100%25' fill='%23f3f4f6'/><text x='50%25' y='50%25' dominant-baseline='middle' text-anchor='middle' fill='%239ca3af' font-family='Inter, Arial' font-size='16'>Image — Rider Safety</text></svg>"/>
          <h3 class="mb-2">5) Road safety & social acceptability (license to operate)</h3>
          <p class="muted mb-2"><strong>Observation:</strong> Two‑wheel incidents are closely watched; authorities and public scrutinize courier conditions.</p>
          <p class="muted mb-2"><strong>Risk:</strong> Incidents cause service disruption and reputation shock; high rider turnover increases delivery time variance.</p>
          <p class="mb-2"><strong>Strategic comms angle:</strong> Rider Safety Charter + published indicators (PPE, training, incidents per 1,000, red zones); a pro‑city stance (hours/weather/safe dispatch).</p>
          <p class="mb-0"><strong>Growth impact:</strong> Higher rider retention (capacity), steadier delivery times (experience), stronger local acceptability (market access/partnerships).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <img class="gap-ph" alt="Placeholder — Care‑first Support" loading="lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='640' height='240'><rect width='100%25' height='100%25' fill='%23f3f4f6'/><text x='50%25' y='50%25' dominant-baseline='middle' text-anchor='middle' fill='%239ca3af' font-family='Inter, Arial' font-size='16'>Image — Care‑first Support</text></svg>"/>
          <h3 class="mb-2">6) Customer care & claims (sensitivity, speed, repair)</h3>
          <p class="muted mb-2"><strong>Observation:</strong> In Morocco, empathy (FR/AR/Darija) and resolution speed matter as much as operations.</p>
          <p class="muted mb-2"><strong>Risk:</strong> Poorly handled incidents erase logistics value and can trigger viral negativity.</p>
          <p class="mb-2"><strong>Strategic comms angle:</strong> Public service promise (ack ≤15’, first reply ≤60’, target resolution ≤24h); empathetic scripts; public closure for socially visible cases.</p>
          <p class="mb-0"><strong>Growth impact:</strong> Turn incidents into loyalty (repeat), reduce bad buzz (protect acquisition), increase post‑claim CSAT.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Transversal read & value proposition -->
    <section class="container" id="frame" aria-labelledby="frame-title">
      <h2 id="frame-title">A communicable trust architecture</h2>
      <p class="mb-2">Rules of the game (1) → Respect for people & data (2,6) → Checkout protection (3) → Verifiable quality (4) → City & riders protected (5). Each brick targets a specific growth bottleneck by moving proof to the foreground.</p>
      <div class="card" style="margin-top:16px">
        <h3 class="mb-2">Value proposition</h3>
        <p class="mb-0">I help convert trust into growth. We formalize and publish proof where friction lives (rules, data, payment, quality, safety, service). Outcome: more restaurants signing, more digital payments passing, fewer claims, more repeat — and a Moroccan brand perceived as fair, reliable, and responsible.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 90‑Day plan -->
    <section class="container" id="plan" aria-labelledby="plan-title">
      <h2 id="plan-title">90‑Day Plan — outcomes, not tasks</h2>
      <p class="muted mb-6">Each phase has one clear outcome and KPI. Built to deliver fast and de‑risk decision‑making.</p>
      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step card">
          <h3 class="mb-2">0–30 days — Foundation & Proof</h3>
          <p class="mb-2"><strong>Outcome:</strong> Trust assets v1 (Fair‑Play Charter, Privacy & Ranking Note) aligned with leadership; stakeholder map; press explainer by week 2.</p>
          <p class="mb-0"><strong>KPI:</strong> Alignment confirmed; first earned mention or strategic placement.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step card">
          <h3 class="mb-2">31–60 days — Publishing Engine</h3>
          <p class="mb-2"><strong>Outcome:</strong> Editorial cadence + executive LinkedIn voice; six‑week roadmap; monthly barometers (refunds, quality).</p>
          <p class="mb-0"><strong>KPI:</strong> Cadence established; list growth; tier‑2 mentions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step card">
          <h3 class="mb-2">61–90 days — Authority & Scale</h3>
          <p class="mb-2"><strong>Outcome:</strong> Anchor op‑ed/panel; quantified case‑proof; crisis drill (FR/AR).</p>
          <p class="mb-0"><strong>KPI:</strong> Tier‑1 mention or high‑value speaking slot; response time &lt; 30 min.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

